Animal defers to tier, and with different connotations, Bestie. In general, it is the figure of animality to describe aspects of the human, for example, virtues, vices, drives or types. Sometimes, 'animal' means 'animal' in itself, but especially in its appendices the savagely, with no end of suffering or self-loathing. The most famous use of the beast is in the denigration of the self and its higher spirits, the symbol of greedily using a serpent as a symbol of recruitment, etc. This denigration, in turn, denigrated the noble type; thus, the ‘animal’ is the original form of humanity but also with its ‘higher spirits’. The denigration of the noble kind is also found in the ‘evil’. The dog is something that is not productive for human beings, but is nevertheless important. The dog is a piece of metaphysics that misunderstands the role of sentiment in art, music, etc. This denigration of the noble class can be found in accounts of the sickness that brings about the death of virtues. 

